  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Poor oral hygiene is associated with respiratory pathogen colonization and secondary lung
      infection.The possible association between oral care and incidence of VAP, and the role of
      dental plaque, mouth and tracheal colonization have not been firmly established. The
      investigators' hypothesis was that improving oral care with electrical toothbrushing might be
      effective in reducing the incidence of VAP.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
